mrigger added on 2019-12-23 23:19:27:
Consider the following test case:
CREATE TABLE t0(c0 TEXT, CHECK(c0 BETWEEN 0 AND +c0));
INSERT INTO t0 VALUES (0);
UPDATE t0 SET c0 = 0; -- sqlite3.c:86402: sqlite3VdbeExec: Assertion `pIn1!=pIn3' failed.
When compiling with -DSQLITE_DEBUG, the UPDATE triggers an assertion error. This might be related to https://www.sqlite.org/src/tktview?name=188f912b51.
